    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-19T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-19T23:00:00-05:00" n="327"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 E.W./10–1744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-20T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 20, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8719. For Murphy. The Department has considered your 8842, October 17, 6 p.m.,
                    and believes that the high policy decisions implicit in certain of the points
                    made will necessitate a reference of this matter to the White House. Pending
                    such reference the Department agrees that no broadcasts or announcements should
                    be made which could be <pb facs="0576" n="562" xml:id="pg_562"/> construed as a
                    general commitment or long-term obligation toward Germany or the German people.
                    However, the Department feels that your suggestion regarding a blackout on
                    propaganda is impracticable at this time. It does agree that the maximum
                    possible amount of straight news presentation will be desirable.</p>
                <p>The last paragraph of your telegram under reference will be discussed with the
                    Office of War Information and the War Department and our joint decision will be
                    telegraphed to you at a later date. In general the Department is inclined to
                    favor the inclusion of OWI civilians and the maximum possible OWI responsibility
                    for operations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
